The paper discusses a framework for robotic manipulation, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of ontologies for semantic-based inference suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) in the proposed framework. The paper also mentions the use of physics-based engines, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) for object recognition and tracking. Finally, the need to work with a low integration step to find accurate solutions suggests the involvement of control systems (cs.SY) in the proposed framework.
